list.comment: Tried KNN based smoothing using samples of human responses. Seems insufficient

MESSAGE.value: Minorly fixing bugs and removing issues.
Seem to have most bugs worked out. Ready for another run, I think.
Simulations now draw samples from the true distribution of tired turkers. This means that we're going to get correct, if pessimistic, results.
CRF now adds human observation factors based on observed human distribution. Engine has access to both error and delay distributions, which are configurable. Refactored distribution locations.
Added an overall F1 and per class F1 to get a better handle on performance.
Making ThresholdHeuristic much more aggressive, running with a huge pool of workers, seeing what happens.
Added cacheing, stubbed out MCTS, etc
Lookahead one heuristic seems to work well, if horrendously slowly.
Initial version of MCTS with Double Progressive Widening is implemented, with a dummy harness for testing. Still needs debugging, results don't make sense.
Normalizing and rescaling loss as reward in [0,1] for UCB1 to work properly, now need to think up some more clever tests.
Updated the way GameState and MCTS handle in flight request sampling, now works on NER. Moving on to confidence estimation, which is clearly broken right now.
Have KNN normalization working, and it seems to actually do good work.
Multithreading sampling, and fixing issues with time.
Have some universal logs started. Interesting race conditions causing problems.
Wrote the outline of an argument about bounds I was up all night thinking about. Still need some of the derivations. But this is potentially actually useful.
Minor typo fix.
Seem to have fixed a hashing race condition. Subtle subtle scala.
Dumping example logs for human classification errors. Also added a 2-class tutorial, for a very skeptical Turk run.
Running a test against the real Turkers with 2-class NER. Person, location, nothing.
Starting to stub out machinery for face-matching problem.
Now downloading, processing, and cacheing embeddings. Hopefully this produces a runnable set.
Fixed broken build bug
Half way through piping knn normalization flag.
Adding person recognition embeddings data cache.
Further tweaking PersonUseCase in preparation for doing real runs. Now need bin tuning for single node graphs.
